						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Ballāḷa III: A.D. 1320.</hi></p>						

						<p>Gift of land situated close to a tank called Koṅgiṇi-kiṟai to Vīṟṟirunda Perumāḷ at Koḷḷagar <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> [Tribhu]vana-mādēvichchaturvēdimaṅgalam, by a dancing girl <hi rend="italic">(taḷiyilāḷ)</hi> of Muḍikoṇḍīśvaramuḍaiyār temple at Muḍikoṇḍachōḻapuram <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Dēśiyuyyakkoṇḍachōḻa-paṭṭaṇam in Padi-nāḍu. The two members of the regiment namely, Vīrachōḻavaṇukkar and Vīrakoḍiyar were to protect the grant.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">E.C.</hi> (n), Vol. IV, No. Kol. 5.</p>						

						</summary>
